## 6. Advanced Memory Architecture

Memory recall utilizes an exponential decay curve combining importance and time-delta since last access:

$$S_{recall} = I \times e^{-\lambda t}$$

Where:
- $I$: Estimated importance (1.0 to 5.0).
- $\lambda$: Half-life decay constant.
- $t$: Time difference since $last\_accessed\_at$.

### Consolidation Workflow
Short-term memory blocks generated during chat runs are periodically aggregated by an LLM cron task into permanent, structured profile nodes, updating User preferences automatically.

