## 9. Multi-Agent & Autonomous Loop Architecture

We construct a LangGraph cyclical graph that supports recursive reflection:

```mermaid
graph TD
    Start([User Request]) --> MemoryNode[💾 Memory Node]
    MemoryNode --> Planner[🧠 Planner Node]
    Planner --> Router{"🔀 Router"}
    
    Router -->|execute step| ToolNode["🛠️ Tool Executor Node"]
    ToolNode --> Evaluate{"🤔 Evaluation Gate"}
    
    Evaluate -->|success| NextStep[Update State Step Index]
    NextStep --> Planner
    
    Evaluate -->|failure / mismatch| Replan["🔄 Re-planning Node"]
    Replan --> Planner
    
    Router -->|plan finished| Response["✏️ Response Compiler"]
    Response --> End([Final Output])
```

The system evaluates tool results. If execution encounters an error (e.g. file not found, API timeout), the `Re-planning Node` dynamically edits the remaining plan queue and selects alternative tool options before attempting execution again.

